The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi, March 7 (PTI): The government is mulling the idea of roping in the CISF for screening check-in baggage of private airline passengers. Presently, the airlines themselves carry out the screening. 

 The proposal follows incidents of firearms finding their way into aircraft. The matter is being discussed. However, no decision has emerged so far, CISF director-general S.I.S. Ahmed said today.

 New Delhi (PTI): A man who had submitted a fake CBSE marksheet while seeking admission to Delhi Universitys Hans Raj College twelve years ago has been convicted by a local court for cheating and forgery. Ayush Jain claimed he himself had been duped with the fake marksheet.

 Flight snag

 nai (PTI) A Mumbai-bound GoAir flight, with 150 people on board, aborted its journey just before taking off on Wednesday. The Airbus A320 aircraft developed a fault on the runway, airport sources said. Everyone on board is safe. 

 Hyderabad (PTI): The CBI has arrested an air force employee here for alleged corruption. S. Babu Rao, the personal assistant to the air officer commanding Hakimpet Air Force Station, was caught taking Rs 20,000 from the complainant for an official favour, sources said.

 Panaji (PTI): The anti-narcotics cell of Goa police has arrested a citizen of Nepal for peddling charas and seized 5 kg of the contraband from him. Anesh Dal Bahadur Bhandari, 40, was arrested in Bardez, where he was delivering a consignment.

 Jammu: (PTI): The Mata Vaishnodevi Shrine Board has roped in Bharat Petroleum Corporation to issue registration slips through its outlets.




